Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.02,0:00:21.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,and was working on population trends.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.02,0:00:21.76,CHN,,0,0,0,,正在研究人口趋势
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.76,0:00:24.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,They showed a reprint to their former classmates
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.76,0:00:24.04,CHN,,0,0,0,,统计学家拿出一篇文章给老同学看
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.04,0:00:27.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,and the reprint started as usual with the Gaussian distribution.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.04,0:00:27.24,CHN,,0,0,0,,开篇就是一个平淡无奇的正态分布
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.24,0:00:29.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,The statistician explained to the former classmate
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.24,0:00:29.88,CHN,,0,0,0,,统计学家向自己的老同学逐一解释
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.88,0:00:31.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,the meaning of the symbols for
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.88,0:00:31.42,CHN,,0,0,0,,那些式子表示的含义{\fsp0}——
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.42,0:00:34.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,the actual population, the average population and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.42,0:00:34.58,CHN,,0,0,0,,实际人口、平均人口…等等
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.98,0:00:37.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,The classmate was a bit incredulous
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.98,0:00:37.02,CHN,,0,0,0,,同学有点怀疑
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.02,0:00:40.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,and was not quite sure whether the statistician was pulling their leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.02,0:00:40.00,CHN,,0,0,0,,不确定统计学家是不是在捉弄她
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.00,0:00:42.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,"How can you know that?" was the query
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.00,0:00:42.00,CHN,,0,0,0,,“你是怎么知道的？”  她问
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.00,0:00:43.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,and "What is this symbol over here?"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.00,0:00:43.94,CHN,,0,0,0,,“那里的那个符号又是什么？”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.94,0:00:45.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Oh", said the statistician.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.94,0:00:45.82,CHN,,0,0,0,,“噢”  统计学家回答
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.82,0:00:47.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,"This is π."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.82,0:00:47.02,CHN,,0,0,0,,“这是 π”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.02,0:00:48.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,"What is that?"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.02,0:00:48.50,CHN,,0,0,0,,“π 是什么？”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.50,0:00:51.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,"The ratio of the circumference of a circle to its diameter."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.50,0:00:51.75,CHN,,0,0,0,,“圆的周长和直径的比值”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.75,0:00:54.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Well, now you're pushing the joke too far.", said the classmate.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.75,0:00:54.60,CHN,,0,0,0,,“啊这  你这玩笑太过分了”  同学说
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.60,0:00:58.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Surely, the population has nothing to do with the circumference of the circle."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.60,0:00:58.30,CHN,,0,0,0,,“……人口又怎么可能跟圆的周长扯上关系呢！”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.12,0:01:01.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,In the paper, Wigner then goes on to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.12,0:01:01.42,CHN,,0,0,0,,在他这篇论文中  魏格纳接下来讨论了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.42,0:01:04.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,the more general phenomenon of concepts in pure math
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.42,0:01:04.00,CHN,,0,0,0,,在纯数学领域  普遍存在的一个现象{\fsp-33}：
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.00,0:01:06.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,seeming to find applications that extend strangely beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.00,0:01:06.88,CHN,,0,0,0,,纯数学有许多概念  应用得似乎太广了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.88,0:01:08.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,what their definitions would suggest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.88,0:01:08.75,CHN,,0,0,0,,远远超出了原本的定义
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.75,0:01:11.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,But I would like to stay focused on this particular anecdote
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.75,0:01:11.90,CHN,,0,0,0,,但我想继续关注这段轶事中
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.90,0:01:14.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,and the question that the statistician's friend is getting at.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.90,0:01:14.72,CHN,,0,0,0,,这位统计学家的朋友提出的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.72,0:01:17.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,You see, there is a very beautiful and classic proof
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.72,0:01:17.50,CHN,,0,0,0,,有一个美妙的经典证明
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.48,0:01:21.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,that explains the π inside the formula for a normal distribution
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.50,0:01:21.04,CHN,,0,0,0,,解释了正态分布的式子中离奇出现的 π
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.04,0:01:24.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,and despite there being a number of other really great explanations online
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.04,0:01:24.76,CHN,,0,0,0,,虽然网上已经有了无数相当酷炫的解释
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.76,0:01:26.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,see some links in the description
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.76,0:01:26.50,CHN,,0,0,0,,相关链接请看评论区
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.50,0:01:28.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,I cannot help but indulge in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.50,0:01:28.08,CHN,,0,0,0,,但我还是忍不住在这里
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.08,0:01:30.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,the pleasure of reanimating it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.08,0:01:30.08,CHN,,0,0,0,,不厌其烦地将它重新演绎一遍
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.08,0:01:32.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,For one thing, there is a fun side note that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.08,0:01:32.06,CHN,,0,0,0,,一方面  很有意思的是
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.05,0:01:34.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,I didn't learn until recently about how you can use this proof
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.06,0:01:34.90,CHN,,0,0,0,,我最近才知道  可以利用这个证明思路
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.90,0:01:37.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,to derive the volumes of higher dimensional spheres.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.90,0:01:37.50,CHN,,0,0,0,,来求出高维空间中球的体积 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.14,0:01:40.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,But much more importantly than that, what I really want to do
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.14,0:01:40.86,CHN,,0,0,0,,但更重要的  也是我真正想做的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.86,0:01:43.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,is try to go beyond the classic proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.86,0:01:43.14,CHN,,0,0,0,,是努力超越这个经典证明
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.14,0:01:46.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Consider this hypothetical statistician's friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.14,0:01:46.14,CHN,,0,0,0,,面对这个故事中统计学家的朋友
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.14,0:01:47.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,What I want to ask is,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.14,0:01:47.48,CHN,,0,0,0,,我想问的是
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.48,0:01:50.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,can we find an explanation that would satisfy their disbelief?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.48,0:01:50.90,CHN,,0,0,0,,能否找到让这位朋友心悦诚服的解答？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.90,0:01:53.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,You see, they're not just asking for some pure math proof
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.90,0:01:53.62,CHN,,0,0,0,,毕竟  这位朋友想要的不是用数学去证明
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.62,0:01:56.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,about a function that was handed down to them on high.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.62,0:01:56.24,CHN,,0,0,0,,一个从天而降的函数的性质
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.24,0:01:58.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,The friend's incredulity
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.24,0:01:58.02,CHN,,0,0,0,,她真正不相信的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.02,0:02:01.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,was that circles should have anything to do with population statistics.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.02,0:02:01.80,CHN,,0,0,0,,是 “圆” 和 {\fsp-3}“{\fsp2}人口统计” 之间的关联
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.80,0:02:04.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,Until we fully draw that connecting line,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.80,0:02:04.40,CHN,,0,0,0,,在完全呈现这种关联之前
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.40,0:02:06.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,we should consider the task incomplete.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.40,0:02:06.58,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们需要回顾之前未完成的任务
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.58,0:02:09.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Those of you who watched the last video on the Central Limit Theorem
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.58,0:02:09.60,CHN,,0,0,0,,看过之前中心极限定理那期视频的观众们
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.60,0:02:11.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,will have some of the backdrop here
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.60,0:02:11.34,CHN,,0,0,0,,可能已经了解了一些背景知识
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.34,0:02:14.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,because there we broke down the formula for a normal distribution,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.34,0:02:14.42,CHN,,0,0,0,,因为在那期视频里  我们剖析了正态分布
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.42,0:02:17.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,which is also called a Gaussian Distribution
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.42,0:02:17.00,CHN,,0,0,0,,或称高斯分布的数学表达式
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.00,0:02:20.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,and when you strip away all of the different parameters and the constants,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.00,0:02:20.70,CHN,,0,0,0,,剥去各种各样的参数和常量之后
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.70,0:02:25.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,the basic function that describes the bell curve shape is e^-x²
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.70,0:02:25.32,CHN,,0,0,0,,描述钟形曲线的基本函数  就是 e 的 -x² 次方
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.90,0:02:28.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,And the reason that π showed up in the final formula
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.90,0:02:28.88,CHN,,0,0,0,,而 π 之所以出现在最终的式子里
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.88,0:02:32.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,was that the area underneath this curve works out,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.88,0:02:32.06,CHN,,0,0,0,,就是因为  这条曲线下的面积的值
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.06,0:02:33.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,as you will see in a couple minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.06,0:02:33.86,CHN,,0,0,0,,你们很快就会发现
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.86,0:02:35.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,to be the √π.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.86,0:02:35.50,CHN,,0,0,0,,正是 {\fs0.001}l{\fs66\fsp0}√(pi)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.24,0:02:37.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,So, what that meant for us was that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.24,0:02:37.84,CHN,,0,0,0,,因此  这就意味着
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.84,0:02:40.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,at some point we needed to divide out by that √π
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.84,0:02:40.40,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们需要除掉这个 {\fs0.001}l{\fs66\fsp0}√(pi)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.40,0:02:43.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,to make sure that the area under the curve is 1,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.40,0:02:43.04,CHN,,0,0,0,,来确保曲线下的面积为 1
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.04,0:02:44.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,which is a requirement
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.16,0:02:46.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,before you can interpret it as a probability distribution.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.04,0:02:46.80,CHN,,0,0,0,,满足这一点  我们才能将其视为概率分布
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.40,0:02:50.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,In the full formula that you would see, say in a stats book,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.40,0:02:50.70,CHN,,0,0,0,,你在统计学课本里  看见的完整式子中
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.70,0:02:53.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,this gets mixed together with some of the other constants.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.70,0:02:53.40,CHN,,0,0,0,,π 和一些其他常数搅在了一起
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.40,0:02:54.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,But in its purest form,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.40,0:02:54.94,CHN,,0,0,0,,但在最纯粹的形式中
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.94,0:02:58.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,that π originates from the area underneath this curve.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.94,0:02:58.16,CHN,,0,0,0,,π 来源于这条曲线下的面积
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.86,0:03:00.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,So, step number one for you and me
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.86,0:03:00.98,CHN,,0,0,0,,因此  我们要做的第一步就是
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.98,0:03:02.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,is to explain that area.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.98,0:03:02.64,CHN,,0,0,0,,阐明怎么求这个面积
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.64,0:03:05.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,But I want to emphasize it's not the last step.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.64,0:03:05.12,CHN,,0,0,0,,但我要在此强调  这不是最后一步
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.12,0:03:09.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,To satisfy the question raised by that hypothetical statistician's friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.12,0:03:09.36,CHN,,0,0,0,,为了回应统计学家的朋友的质疑
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.36,0:03:10.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,we need to go further.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.36,0:03:10.55,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们不能止步于此
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.55,0:03:11.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,We need to also answer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.55,0:03:11.90,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们还需要指出
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.90,0:03:15.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,why is it that this function e^-x² from is so special in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.90,0:03:15.96,CHN,,0,0,0,,函数“e 的 -x² 次方”究竟为什么会如此特殊
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.96,0:03:19.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,I mean, there are lots of different formulas you could write down
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.96,0:03:19.00,CHN,,0,0,0,,你看  明明有许多不同的式子
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.00,0:03:21.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,that would give a shape that you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.00,0:03:21.06,CHN,,0,0,0,,都能描述这种
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.06,0:03:24.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,vaguely bulges in the middle and tapers out on either side.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.06,0:03:24.22,CHN,,0,0,0,,中间突起  两边平稳下降的形状
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.22,0:03:26.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,So why is it that this specific function
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.22,0:03:26.86,CHN,,0,0,0,,但为什么偏偏这个函数
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.86,0:03:28.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,holds such a special place in statistics?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.86,0:03:28.90,CHN,,0,0,0,,在统计学中独领风骚{\fsp-33}？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.62,0:03:31.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,To phrase our goal another way
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.62,0:03:31.26,CHN,,0,0,0,,换句话说  我们的目标是
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.26,0:03:33.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,can we find a connection
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.26,0:03:33.02,CHN,,0,0,0,,能否找到一种解释
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.02,0:03:35.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,between the proof that shows why π shows up
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.02,0:03:35.50,CHN,,0,0,0,,把“π 出现原因的证明”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.50,0:03:37.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,and the Central Limit Theorem
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.50,0:03:37.30,CHN,,0,0,0,,和“中心极限定理”联系起来
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.30,0:03:39.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,which, as we talked about in the last video,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.30,0:03:39.56,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们上期视频讲过
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.56,0:03:40.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,is the thing that explains
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.56,0:03:40.94,CHN,,0,0,0,,这个定理解释了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.94,0:03:44.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,when you can expect a normal distribution to arise in nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.94,0:03:44.04,CHN,,0,0,0,,正态分布何时会在自然地出现
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.88,0:03:46.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,So, with all of that is the goal
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.88,0:03:46.20,CHN,,0,0,0,,那么  带着这些目标
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.20,0:03:49.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,first things first, let's dig into the classic and very beautiful proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.20,0:03:49.30,CHN,,0,0,0,,首先  我们来仔细看看经典而美妙的证明
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.96,0:03:54.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Alright. When you want to find the area underneath the curve,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.96,0:03:54.76,CHN,,0,0,0,,好  要想求解曲线下的面积
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.76,0:03:57.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,the tool for doing that is an integral.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.76,0:03:57.00,CHN,,0,0,0,,用到的数学工具自然是积分
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.00,0:03:59.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,As a quick reminder for how you might read this notation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.00,0:03:59.66,CHN,,0,0,0,,快速回顾一下  这个式子就是说
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.66,0:04:01.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,you might imagine approximating that area
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.66,0:04:01.82,CHN,,0,0,0,,你可以用曲线下的许多小矩形
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.82,0:04:03.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,with many different rectangles under the curve
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.82,0:04:03.62,CHN,,0,0,0,,去逼近所要求的面积
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.62,0:04:05.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,where the height of each such rectangle
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.86,0:04:07.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,is the value of the function above that point,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.62,0:04:07.96,CHN,,0,0,0,,每个小矩形的高  就是在那个点处的函数值
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.96,0:04:10.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,in this case e^-x² for a certain input x
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.96,0:04:10.94,CHN,,0,0,0,,在这里就是给定 x 后   e 的 -x² 次方的值
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.94,0:04:13.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,and the width is some little number that we're calling dx.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.94,0:04:13.94,CHN,,0,0,0,,矩形的宽是个很小的数  我们将其记为 dx
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.58,0:04:17.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,We need to add up the areas of all these rectangles
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.58,0:04:17.20,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们需要把所有矩形的面积加起来
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.20,0:04:20.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,for values of x ranging from -∞ up to ∞
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.20,0:04:20.46,CHN,,0,0,0,,x的范围取从 -∞ 到 ∞
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.46,0:04:22.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,and the use of that notation dx is kind of meant to imply
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.46,0:04:22.46,CHN,,0,0,0,,dx 这个记号就是在提醒你
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.46,0:04:25.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,you shouldn't think of any specific width
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.46,0:04:25.32,CHN,,0,0,0,,不要把小宽度看作是固定的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.32,0:04:29.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,but instead you ask as the chosen width for your rectangle gets thinner and thinner,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.32,0:04:29.34,CHN,,0,0,0,,而是去考虑  当选择的宽度越来越窄时
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.34,0:04:32.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,what does this sum of all those areas approach?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.34,0:04:32.06,CHN,,0,0,0,,所有面积的和会趋于什么值
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.06,0:04:34.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Of course, all of that is just notation
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.06,0:04:34.18,CHN,,0,0,0,,当然  这些都只是抽象记号
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.18,0:04:36.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,unless you provide a way to answer that question
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.18,0:04:36.45,CHN,,0,0,0,,关键是  要如何求出这个极限呢
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.45,0:04:39.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,and the magic of calculus is that it provides just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.45,0:04:39.36,CHN,,0,0,0,,这个问题的答案  正是微积分的精髓
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.36,0:04:40.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,At least usually.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.36,0:04:40.60,CHN,,0,0,0,,至少通常是能算的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.60,0:04:42.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,You see, usually the procedure here
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.60,0:04:42.82,CHN,,0,0,0,,通常的步骤是
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.82,0:04:44.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,would be to find some function
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.82,0:04:44.56,CHN,,0,0,0,,先去找到另一个函数
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.56,0:04:48.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,whose derivative is equal to the stuff we have on the inside, e^-x².
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.56,0:04:48.76,CHN,,0,0,0,,使得导数等于里头的被积函数   e 的 -x² 次方
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.76,0:04:52.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,In other words, we want to find an antiderivative of that function.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.76,0:04:52.18,CHN,,0,0,0,,换句话说  我们想求的是这个函数的原函数
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.18,0:04:54.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,The problem is, for this particular function,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.18,0:04:54.66,CHN,,0,0,0,,问题在于  对这个函数而言
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.66,0:04:58.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,it is provably not possible to find such an antiderivative.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.66,0:04:58.32,CHN,,0,0,0,,可以证明  不可能找到这个原函数的表达式
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.32,0:04:59.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's a little weird and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.32,0:04:59.80,CHN,,0,0,0,,听起来有点奇怪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.80,0:05:01.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,beyond the scope of what I want to talk about here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.80,0:05:01.82,CHN,,0,0,0,,也超过了这期视频的讨论范围
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.82,0:05:04.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,But basically, even though there exists an antiderivative,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.82,0:05:04.56,CHN,,0,0,0,,虽然原函数本身是存在的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.56,0:05:06.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,it is a well-defined function.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.56,0:05:06.32,CHN,,0,0,0,,是一个有定义的函数
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.32,0:05:10.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,You cannot express what that antiderivative is using all our usual tools
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.32,0:05:10.36,CHN,,0,0,0,,但你就是没法把原函数表达成通常的函数
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.36,0:05:13.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,like polynomial expressions, trig functions, exponentials
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.36,0:05:13.36,CHN,,0,0,0,,比如  多项式  三角函数  指数函数  等等
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.36,0:05:14.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,or any way to mix them together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.36,0:05:14.92,CHN,,0,0,0,,及其任意的组合
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.92,0:05:17.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,So, finding this area requires a bit of cleverness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.92,0:05:17.48,CHN,,0,0,0,,因此  求这个面积需要一点技巧
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.48,0:05:19.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,There needs to be a new trick that we bring to bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.48,0:05:19.76,CHN,,0,0,0,,这里我们要整点新花招
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.76,0:05:22.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,And the first step to this trick is easily the most absurd.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.76,0:05:22.56,CHN,,0,0,0,,第一步看起来尤为荒谬
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.56,0:05:24.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,We start by bumping things up one dimension,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.56,0:05:24.86,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们先把这个式子提高一维
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.86,0:05:27.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,so that instead of asking for the area under a bell curve,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.86,0:05:27.76,CHN,,0,0,0,,这样我们要求的就不再是钟形{\u1}曲线{\u0}下的{\u1}面积{\u0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.76,0:05:32.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,we ask for the volume underneath this kind of bell surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.76,0:05:32.48,CHN,,0,0,0,, 而是这样的钟形{\u1}曲面{\u0}下的{\u1}体积{\u0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.48,0:05:33.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,You could rightly ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.48,0:05:33.44,CHN,,0,0,0,,你当然会问
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.44,0:05:35.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Why would you do that? Who ordered another dimension?"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.44,0:05:35.98,CHN,,0,0,0,,“搞什么？谁指使你再加一个维度的？”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.98,0:05:38.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I'll admit, it's not terribly motivated right now
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.98,0:05:38.72,CHN,,0,0,0,,我也只能承认  现在的动机确实不太充分
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.72,0:05:41.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,other than to say watch what happens when we just try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.72,0:05:41.48,CHN,,0,0,0,,只能走一步看一步  看看会发生什么
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.48,0:05:43.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,And in general with hard problems,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.48,0:05:43.20,CHN,,0,0,0,,大而化之  对于难题
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.20,0:05:46.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,it's never a bad idea to try solving "cousins" of the problem
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.20,0:05:46.22,CHN,,0,0,0,,先尝试解决类似的问题  也不失为一个好主意
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.22,0:05:48.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,since that can help you get a little bit of momentum and insight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.22,0:05:48.68,CHN,,0,0,0,,因为这能给你多一点动力和启发
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.46,0:05:52.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,To be clear on how this higher dimensional function is defined
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.46,0:05:52.16,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们来理清这个高维函数是如何定义的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.16,0:05:54.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,it takes in two different inputs, X and Y,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.16,0:05:54.78,CHN,,0,0,0,,它有两个变量 x 和 y
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.78,0:05:57.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,which we might think of as a point on the XY plane
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.78,0:05:57.26,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们可以视其为 XY 平面上的点
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.26,0:05:59.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,and the way to think about it is to consider
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.06,0:06:01.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,the distance from that point to the origin,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.26,0:06:01.20,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们的思路是  考虑这个点到原点的距离
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.20,0:06:02.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,which I'll label as "r"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.20,0:06:02.56,CHN,,0,0,0,,我将这个距离记为 r
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.56,0:06:05.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,and then to plug in that distance to our original bell curve function.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.56,0:06:05.98,CHN,,0,0,0,,然后将这个距离  代入一开始的钟形曲线函数中
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.98,0:06:08.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,That is, we take e to the negative r².
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.98,0:06:08.64,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们得到了 e 的 -r² 次方
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.64,0:06:10.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,You might notice the lines I've drawn on this diagram
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.64,0:06:10.88,CHN,,0,0,0,,你可能会注意到我在图上所画的线
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.88,0:06:12.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,make a right triangle,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.88,0:06:12.46,CHN,,0,0,0,,形成了一个直角三角形
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.46,0:06:16.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,so by the Pythagorean theorem, x²+y²=r².
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.46,0:06:16.42,CHN,,0,0,0,,所以根据勾股定理  x{\fsp16}²+{\fsp4}y{\fsp16}²={\fsp4}r²
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.42,0:06:19.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,So, in the function I have written where you see x²+y²,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.42,0:06:19.96,CHN,,0,0,0,,所以在上面所写的函数中  只要你看到 x{\fsp16}²+{\fsp4}y{\fsp16}²
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.96,0:06:21.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,you can think in the back of your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.96,0:06:21.34,CHN,,0,0,0,,你就可以把它当作
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.34,0:06:24.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,that's really the square of the distance from the point to the origin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.34,0:06:24.70,CHN,,0,0,0,,(x,y)点到原点距离的平方
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.70,0:06:27.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,The main thing to notice here is how this gives our function
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.70,0:06:27.10,CHN,,0,0,0,,注意看  这样定义的新函数
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.10,0:06:29.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,a kind of circular symmetry
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.10,0:06:29.02,CHN,,0,0,0,,自然就有了圆周对称性
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.02,0:06:33.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,int the sense that all of the inputs that sit on a given circle have the same output.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.02,0:06:33.30,CHN,,0,0,0,,即  同一个圆上的所有点  函数值都相等
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.30,0:06:36.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,And so, when we graph this function in three dimensions,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.30,0:06:36.24,CHN,,0,0,0,,并且这样一来  在三维空间中画函数曲面时
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.24,0:06:39.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,it means it has a rotational symmetry about the Z axis.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.24,0:06:39.26,CHN,,0,0,0,,图像就具有关于 Z 轴的旋转对称性
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.24,0:06:42.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,Math tends to reward you when you respect its symmetries.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.24,0:06:42.90,CHN,,0,0,0,,数学女神偏爱那些敬重她对称之美的人
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.90,0:06:46.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,So for a question of computing the volume underneath the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.90,0:06:46.22,CHN,,0,0,0,,所以为了计算这个曲面下方的体积
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.22,0:06:48.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,what we're going to do is respect that symmetry
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.22,0:06:48.54,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们要做的是利用对称性
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.54,0:06:50.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,and imagine integrating together
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.38,0:06:53.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,a bunch of thin little cylinders underneath that surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.54,0:06:53.38,CHN,,0,0,0,,考虑对曲面下一系列同心圆筒进行积分
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.18,0:06:56.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here, making this a little more quantitative,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.18,0:06:56.28,CHN,,0,0,0,,为了量化这个过程
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.28,0:06:59.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,let's focus on just one of those cylindrical shells,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.28,0:06:59.32,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们首先关注一个固定的圆筒
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.32,0:07:03.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,where its area is going to be the circumference of that shell times the height.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.32,0:07:03.32,CHN,,0,0,0,,其侧面积等于圆筒的周长乘以高度
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.32,0:07:06.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,You might imagine it as something like the label on a soup can
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.32,0:07:06.14,CHN,,0,0,0,,你可以把它想象成罐头上的标签纸
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.14,0:07:08.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,that we can unwrap into a rectangle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.14,0:07:08.38,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们可以把它展成一个矩形
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.38,0:07:10.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,The circumference of the cylinder,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.38,0:07:10.10,CHN,,0,0,0,,这个圆筒的周长
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.10,0:07:12.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,which is the top side of that rectangle
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.10,0:07:12.00,CHN,,0,0,0,,也就是矩形的一边
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.00,0:07:14.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,is going to be 2 π times the radius.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.00,0:07:14.22,CHN,,0,0,0,,等于 2π 乘上半径
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.98,0:07:16.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,And then the height of our cylinder,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.98,0:07:16.76,CHN,,0,0,0,,而圆筒的高
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.76,0:07:18.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,the other side of our rectangle
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.76,0:07:18.30,CHN,,0,0,0,,对应着矩形的另外一边
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.30,0:07:20.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,is the height of the surface at this point,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.30,0:07:20.40,CHN,,0,0,0,,正是曲面在这一点上的高度
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.40,0:07:21.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,which by definition
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.40,0:07:21.52,CHN,,0,0,0,,根据定义
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.52,0:07:24.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,is the value of our function associated with that radius,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.52,0:07:24.80,CHN,,0,0,0,,就是我们的函数在该半径处的取值
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.80,0:07:28.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,which like I said earlier, you can think of as e to the negative r².
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.80,0:07:28.60,CHN,,0,0,0,,如我之前所说  函数值是 e 的 -r² 次方
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.26,0:07:30.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now the real way you want to think about this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.26,0:07:30.84,CHN,,0,0,0,,实际上  圆筒不只有侧面积
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.84,0:07:33.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,is to give that a little bit of thickness
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.84,0:07:33.00,CHN,,0,0,0,,还有一个很小的厚度
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.00,0:07:34.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,which we will call "dr"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.00,0:07:34.56,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们记作 dr
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.56,0:07:36.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,so that the volume that it represents
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.56,0:07:36.68,CHN,,0,0,0,,所以圆筒对应的体积
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.68,0:07:39.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,is approximately that area we just looked at
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.68,0:07:39.06,CHN,,0,0,0,,近似为我们先前提到的侧面积
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.06,0:07:41.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,multiplied by this thickness, dr.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.06,0:07:41.28,CHN,,0,0,0,,乘上这个厚度 dr
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.28,0:07:43.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Our task now is to integrate together
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.28,0:07:43.70,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们现在的任务是对这些圆筒积分
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.70,0:07:46.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,or add together all of these different cylinders
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.24,0:07:49.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,as our ranges between zero and infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.70,0:07:49.00,CHN,,0,0,0,,或者说  将半径在 0 到 ∞ 之间的所有圆筒体积相加
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.00,0:07:51.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Or more precisely, we consider what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.00,0:07:51.18,CHN,,0,0,0,,更准确的说  我们考虑的是
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.18,0:07:54.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,as that thickness gets thinner and thinner approaching zero
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.18,0:07:54.24,CHN,,0,0,0,,圆筒越来越薄  厚度 dr 趋于 0 的情形
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.24,0:07:56.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,and we add together the volumes of the many many many different
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.24,0:07:56.98,CHN,,0,0,0,,然后将这茫茫茫茫多的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.98,0:07:59.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,thin cylinders that sit underneath that curve.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.98,0:07:59.06,CHN,,0,0,0,,曲面下薄圆筒的体积相加
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.86,0:08:05.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,You might think "This is just a harder version of what we were looking at earlier. -
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.86,0:08:05.54,CHN,,0,0,0,,你可能觉得  这只是把开始的问题变得更困难了
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.54,0:08:08.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Three dimensions should be more complicated than two."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.54,0:08:08.50,CHN,,0,0,0,,三维应当比二维更复杂
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.50,0:08:11.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,But actually, something very helpful has happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.50,0:08:11.02,CHN,,0,0,0,,但实际上  这时发生了一件好事情
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.02,0:08:14.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,First let me clean up a little by factoring the π outside that integral.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.02,0:08:14.28,CHN,,0,0,0,,首先  可以整理一下  把 π 移到积分外面
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.28,0:08:16.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now the stuff inside that integral,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.28,0:08:16.50,CHN,,0,0,0,,现在积分式内的部分
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.50,0:08:18.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,having picked up this term "2r"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.50,0:08:18.92,CHN,,0,0,0,,因为多了个 2r
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.92,0:08:20.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,does have an antiderivative.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.92,0:08:20.58,CHN,,0,0,0,,反而就有原函数了
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.58,0:08:22.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,We can now apply the usual tactics of calculus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.58,0:08:22.88,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们开始采用微积分的常规操作
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.62,0:08:26.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Specifically, that whole inside expression
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.62,0:08:26.04,CHN,,0,0,0,,具体而言  积分符号中的部分是
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.04,0:08:29.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,is the derivative of negative e to the negative r².
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.04,0:08:29.76,CHN,,0,0,0,,负的（e 的 -r² 次方）的导数
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.76,0:08:33.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,And so, those of comfortable with calculus know what to do from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.76,0:08:33.28,CHN,,0,0,0,,接着  熟悉微积分的观众已经知道怎么做了
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.28,0:08:34.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,We take that antiderivative
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.28,0:08:34.80,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们往这个原函数里面
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.80,0:08:38.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,and plug in the upper bound, which is negative infinity squared
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.80,0:08:38.08,CHN,,0,0,0,,代入积分上界  也就是负 e 的 -∞² 次方
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.08,0:08:39.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,and that gives us zero
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.08,0:08:39.72,CHN,,0,0,0,,得到 0
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.72,0:08:41.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,or speaking a little bit more precisely
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.72,0:08:41.64,CHN,,0,0,0,,或者更准确的说
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.64,0:08:45.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,if you consider the limit of this expression as the input approaches infinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.64,0:08:45.14,CHN,,0,0,0,,考虑这个表达式在变量趋于无穷时的极限
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.14,0:08:46.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,the limiting value is zero
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.14,0:08:46.72,CHN,,0,0,0,,这个极限值为 0
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.72,0:08:49.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,and we subtract off the value of that antiderivative
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.32,0:08:50.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,at the lower bound, zero,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.72,0:08:50.96,CHN,,0,0,0,,然后再减去  原函数在积分下界 0 的取值
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.96,0:08:52.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,which in this case is -1.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.96,0:08:52.56,CHN,,0,0,0,,这里算出来是 -1
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.00,0:08:55.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,So, all in all, the whole integral just works out to be 1,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.00,0:08:55.86,CHN,,0,0,0,,所以最终这个积分的结果就是 1
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.86,0:08:59.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,which means all we're left with is that factor out in front, π.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.86,0:08:59.30,CHN,,0,0,0,,也就是说  整个式子留下的只有积分外的倍数 π
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.30,0:09:03.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Evidently, the volume underneath this bell surface is π.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.30,0:09:03.12,CHN,,0,0,0,,于是  这个钟型曲面下的体积就是 π
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.12,0:09:07.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I'll point out in this case it's not wild that π shows up
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.12,0:09:07.34,CHN,,0,0,0,,要指出的是   π 在这里出现并不奇怪
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.34,0:09:10.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,because the surface has this intrinsic circular symmetry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.34,0:09:10.08,CHN,,0,0,0,,因为这个曲面自带了圆的对称性
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.82,0:09:13.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Still, you might wonder "How does that help us?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.82,0:09:13.48,CHN,,0,0,0,,不过你可能会问  “这有什么用？”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.48,0:09:16.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,As I said, throughout math, if you face a hard problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.48,0:09:16.24,CHN,,0,0,0,,如我之前所说  要想攻克数学中的难关
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.24,0:09:19.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,solving an adjacent problem can be unexpectedly helpful as a next step.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.24,0:09:19.98,CHN,,0,0,0,,先解决一个相近的问题  说不定能铺平前路
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.98,0:09:22.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,And in this case it's helpful not just for building intuition
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.98,0:09:22.96,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们这个例子的意义不止是为了建立直觉
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.96,0:09:25.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,but we can directly relate the three dimensional graph
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.57,0:09:26.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,to our two dimensional graph
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.96,0:09:26.92,CHN,,0,0,0,,还能通过换一个算体积的观点
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.92,0:09:29.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,by analyzing the volume in a second different way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.92,0:09:29.98,CHN,,0,0,0,,直接联系起来三维与二维中的图像
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.26,0:09:34.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,You see, the more general way to approach volumes underneath surfaces
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.26,0:09:34.82,CHN,,0,0,0,,求曲面下体积更通用的方法是
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.82,0:09:37.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,is to think of chopping it up into slices
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.00,0:09:39.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,that are all parallel to one of the axis.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.82,0:09:39.08,CHN,,0,0,0,,将它切分成一个个平行于坐标轴的薄片
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.08,0:09:42.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,For example, all these slices that are parallel to the X axis.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.08,0:09:42.16,CHN,,0,0,0,,例如  画面中这些薄片就都平行于 x 轴
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.94,0:09:48.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,For example, this right here is a slice that corresponds to the plane y=0.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.94,0:09:48.52,CHN,,0,0,0,,再比如  这一个切片对应着平面 y=0
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.52,0:09:50.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,You might notice it looks just like a bell curve
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.52,0:09:50.80,CHN,,0,0,0,,你或许会发现  它长得很像钟型曲线
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.80,0:09:53.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,and if we write out the function, this should actually make a lot of sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.80,0:09:53.90,CHN,,0,0,0,,写出它的函数形式后  你就会发现确实如此
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.90,0:09:56.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,You could just plug in y=0,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.90,0:09:56.00,CHN,,0,0,0,,直接代入 y=0 就行了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.00,0:09:58.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,but to help see what happens with other slices,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.00,0:09:58.24,CHN,,0,0,0,,但为了理解其它切片上的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.24,0:10:00.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,notice how thanks to the rules of exponentiation,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.24,0:10:00.40,CHN,,0,0,0,,注意这里利用指数运算的法则
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.40,0:10:05.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,we could also write function as e to the negative x² times e to the negative y².
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.40,0:10:05.14,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们可以将函数写作“e 的 -x² 次方”乘“e 的 -y² 次方”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.14,0:10:06.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,It factors out nicely.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.14,0:10:06.58,CHN,,0,0,0,,很完美的因式分解
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.26,0:10:09.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,On this slice, that e to the negative y²,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.26,0:10:09.82,CHN,,0,0,0,,在这个切片上 e 的 -y² 次方
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.82,0:10:12.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,is just a number - specifically the number 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.82,0:10:12.50,CHN,,0,0,0,,只是一个数  在这里具体等于 1
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.50,0:10:16.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,So this is the same graph we've seen before, e to the negative x²,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.50,0:10:16.06,CHN,,0,0,0,,所以这和前面的图像相同  也就是 e 的 -x² 次方
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.06,0:10:18.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,meaning that the area of this slice
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.06,0:10:18.14,CHN,,0,0,0,,也就是说这个切片的面积
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.14,0:10:20.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,is exactly the thing that we're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.14,0:10:20.16,CHN,,0,0,0,,就是我们最初要求的积分
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.16,0:10:23.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's the mystery constant which I'm going to give the name "C".
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.16,0:10:23.50,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们姑且称这个神秘常数为 C
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.50,0:10:27.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,What's nice is there is nothing really special about this particular slice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.50,0:10:27.24,CHN,,0,0,0,,很好的一点是  这个切片并没有什么特别的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.24,0:10:31.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,If we chose a different slice corresponding to a different Y value,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.24,0:10:31.06,CHN,,0,0,0,,如果我们选取 y 值不同的另一个切片
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.06,0:10:34.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,it corresponds to multiplying this curve by a different number.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.06,0:10:34.14,CHN,,0,0,0,,就相当于将原本的曲线乘以另一个值
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.14,0:10:35.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,So, it's the same basic shape
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.14,0:10:35.96,CHN,,0,0,0,,所以这些曲线的形状都类似
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.96,0:10:38.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,just scaled down by that number.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.96,0:10:38.00,CHN,,0,0,0,,只是高度被压缩了一个倍数
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.00,0:10:40.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,Meaning its area is the same as our mystery constant
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.00,0:10:40.92,CHN,,0,0,0,,因此  其面积就是神秘常数 C
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.92,0:10:42.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,just scaled down by some number.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.92,0:10:42.82,CHN,,0,0,0,,再乘上一个压缩倍数
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.82,0:10:43.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's pretty cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.82,0:10:43.80,CHN,,0,0,0,,这很带劲
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.80,0:10:46.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,Each one of these slices has the same basic shape
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.80,0:10:46.22,CHN,,0,0,0,,这些切面的基本形状都相同
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.22,0:10:48.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,just rescaled in the vertical direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.22,0:10:48.26,CHN,,0,0,0,,只是在竖直方向被放缩了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.92,0:10:52.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Which by the way is not at all true for most two variable functions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.92,0:10:52.30,CHN,,0,0,0,,顺便一提  绝大多数二元函数并没有该性质
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.30,0:10:54.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is very much dependent on the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.30,0:10:54.52,CHN,,0,0,0,,截面的缩放性质  实际取决于
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.52,0:10:56.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,that we were able to factor our function
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.52,0:10:56.52,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们能否把函数分离成
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.52,0:10:58.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,into one part that's just dependent on the Y
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.52,0:10:58.96,CHN,,0,0,0,,只依赖 y 变量的函数
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.96,0:11:01.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,and another part that's just dependent on the X.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.96,0:11:01.22,CHN,,0,0,0,,乘以只依赖 x 变量的函数
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.96,0:11:05.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, to think about the volume underneath this whole surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.96,0:11:05.33,CHN,,0,0,0,,为了计算这个曲面下方的体积
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.33,0:11:06.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,here's another way we could phrase it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.33,0:11:06.96,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们可以这样来思考
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.96,0:11:08.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're going to compute another integral
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.96,0:11:08.82,CHN,,0,0,0,,下面我们来计算另一个
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.82,0:11:12.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,that ranges from Y equals negative infinity up to infinity
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.82,0:11:12.11,CHN,,0,0,0,,y 从 -∞ 到 ∞ 的积分
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.11,0:11:16.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,where the term inside that integral tells us the area of each one of those slices.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.11,0:11:16.79,CHN,,0,0,0,,被积表达式描述的  是每一个切片的面积
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.79,0:11:19.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,And when we multiply it by a little thickness, dy,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.79,0:11:19.59,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们把每个切片  乘以一个很小的厚度 dy
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.59,0:11:23.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,you might think of it as giving each one of those slices a little bit of volume.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.59,0:11:23.16,CHN,,0,0,0,,可以看作每一个小切片  都有一个小体积
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.16,0:11:27.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,And remember, that term C sitting in front represents the thing we want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.16,0:11:27.64,CHN,,0,0,0,,记住  在前面的 C 项代表了我们想算的切片面积
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.64,0:11:32.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,Which itself is an integral. A suspiciously similar looking integral.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.64,0:11:32.51,CHN,,0,0,0,,因此 C 本身也是一个积分  并且跟 y 的积分过于相似
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.51,0:11:34.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,See, if we take the expression on the top
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.51,0:11:34.40,CHN,,0,0,0,,看  如果我们从上面的表达式里
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.40,0:11:39.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,and we factor out that constant C because it's just a number, it doesn't depend on Y,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.40,0:11:39.32,CHN,,0,0,0,,提取出常数 C {\fs0.001}中{\fs66\fsp0}—— 它是与自变量 y 无关的一个数
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.32,0:11:42.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,the thing we're left with, the integral we need to compute
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.32,0:11:42.22,CHN,,0,0,0,,那么我们所剩下的这个需要计算的积分
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.22,0:11:45.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,is exactly the mystery constant, the thing we don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.22,0:11:45.42,CHN,,0,0,0,,恰好又是神秘常数 C
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.42,0:11:48.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,So, overall, the volume underneath this bell surface
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.42,0:11:48.76,CHN,,0,0,0,,也就是说  这个钟型曲面下方的体积
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.76,0:11:52.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,works out to be this mystery constant squared.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.76,0:11:52.39,CHN,,0,0,0,,就是神秘常数 C 的平方
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.39,0:11:54.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,Out of context, this might seem very unhelpful,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.39,0:11:54.77,CHN,,0,0,0,,抛开上下文  这也许没有什么用
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.77,0:11:58.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,it's just relating one thing we don't know to another thing we don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.77,0:11:58.42,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们只是把一个未知的东西  表达成另一个未知的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.42,0:12:00.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,except we've already computed the volume under this surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.42,0:12:00.99,CHN,,0,0,0,,但是  这个曲面下的体积  我们刚刚算过啊
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.99,0:12:02.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,We know that it's equal to π.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.99,0:12:02.92,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们知道答案等于 π
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.92,0:12:05.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the mystery constant we want to know,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.92,0:12:05.21,CHN,,0,0,0,,因此  这个我们最想计算的神秘常数 C
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.21,0:12:07.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,the area underneath this bell curve,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.21,0:12:07.22,CHN,,0,0,0,,即正态分布曲线下方的面积
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.22,0:12:09.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,must be the square root of π.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.22,0:12:09.03,CHN,,0,0,0,,必须等于 {\fs0.001}l{\fs66\fsp0}√(pi)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.31,0:12:14.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's a very pretty argument but a few things are not entirely satisfying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.31,0:12:14.79,CHN,,0,0,0,,这个论证非常漂亮  可惜不够令人满意
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.79,0:12:17.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,For one thing, it feels a little bit like a trick,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.38,0:12:19.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,something that just happened to work
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.79,0:12:19.23,CHN,,0,0,0,,一方面  这就像一个碰巧行得通的小花招
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.23,0:12:20.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,without offering much of a sense
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.54,0:12:23.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,for how you could have rediscovered it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.23,0:12:23.28,CHN,,0,0,0,,学完后  你还是不知道怎样自己推出这个结论
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.28,0:12:26.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Also, if we think back to our imagined statistician's friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.28,0:12:26.57,CHN,,0,0,0,,另一方面  回想统计学家的朋友
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.57,0:12:28.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,it doesn't really answer their question,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.57,0:12:28.57,CHN,,0,0,0,,这并没有回答她们的问题{\fsp-33}：
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.57,0:12:32.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,which was what do circles have to do with population statistics.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.57,0:12:32.58,CHN,,0,0,0,,“圆”在人口统计学里有什么用
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.58,0:12:35.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Like I said, it's the first step, not the last;
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.58,0:12:35.01,CHN,,0,0,0,,我说过  这只是本视频的第一步
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.01,0:12:37.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,and as our next step, let's see if we can unpack
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.01,0:12:37.07,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们的下一步  就是试着解释
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.07,0:12:40.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,why this proof is not quite as wild and arbitrary as you might first think
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.07,0:12:40.99,CHN,,0,0,0,,为什么这证明并没有想象中那么蛮不讲理
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.99,0:12:42.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,and how it relates to an explanation for
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.99,0:12:42.84,CHN,,0,0,0,,以及如何与函数
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.84,0:12:46.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,where this function e^-x² is coming from in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.84,0:12:46.70,CHN,,0,0,0,,“e 的 -x² 次方”的来源联系在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.74,0:12:56.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,John Herschel was this mathematician/scientist/inventor
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.74,0:12:56.12,CHN,,0,0,0,,{\ko221}约翰·赫歇尔这位数学家{\ko40\4a&HFF&}/{\ko56}科学家{\ko45}/{\ko76}发明家
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.12,0:12:59.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,who really did all sorts of things throughout the 19th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.12,0:12:59.20,CHN,,0,0,0,,在十九世纪可谓是个全才
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.20,0:13:01.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,He made contributions in chemistry,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.06,0:13:03.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,astronomy, photography, botany,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.20,0:13:03.12,CHN,,0,0,0,,{\ko128}他的贡献横跨{\ko59\4a&HFF&}化学  {\ko60}天文学  {\ko76}影像学  {\ko69}植物学
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.12,0:13:04.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,he invented the blueprint
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.12,0:13:04.58,CHN,,0,0,0,,他发明了蓝图
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.58,0:13:07.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,and named many of the moons in our solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.58,0:13:07.44,CHN,,0,0,0,,为太阳系里的诸多卫星取了名字
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.44,0:13:08.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,and in the midst of all of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.44,0:13:08.87,CHN,,0,0,0,,除此之外  在 1850 年
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.87,0:13:11.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,he also offered a very elegant little derivation
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.87,0:13:11.32,CHN,,0,0,0,,他还提出了一种非常精巧的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.32,0:13:13.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,for the Gaussian distribution in 1850.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.32,0:13:13.74,CHN,,0,0,0,,来推导正态分布的式子
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.82,0:13:16.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,the setup is to imagine that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.82,0:13:16.14,CHN,,0,0,0,,他一上来先假设
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.14,0:13:17.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,you want to describe some kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.47,0:13:20.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,probability distribution in two dimensional space.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.14,0:13:20.12,CHN,,0,0,0,,你想描述二维空间里的某种概率分布
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.12,0:13:23.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,For instance maybe you want to model the probability density
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.02,0:13:24.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,for hits on a dartboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.12,0:13:24.82,CHN,,0,0,0,,例如  飞镖击中靶子各处的概率密度
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.82,0:13:25.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,What Herschel showed
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.82,0:13:25.82,CHN,,0,0,0,,赫歇尔证明的是
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.82,0:13:28.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,is that if you want this distribution to satisfy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.82,0:13:28.02,CHN,,0,0,0,,如果要让这个分布
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.02,0:13:30.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,two pretty reasonable seeming properties,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.02,0:13:30.32,CHN,,0,0,0,,满足两个很合理的性质的话
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.32,0:13:32.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,your hand is unexpectedly forced
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.32,0:13:32.36,CHN,,0,0,0,,那实际上没有多少选择的余地了
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.36,0:13:35.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,and even if you had never heard of a Gaussian in your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.36,0:13:35.22,CHN,,0,0,0,,就算你从来没听过正态分布
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.22,0:13:38.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,you would be inexorably drawn to use a function with the shape
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.22,0:13:38.28,CHN,,0,0,0,,只凭两个性质  也会不可避免地得到这种函数
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.28,0:13:40.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,e to the negative x² plus y².
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.28,0:13:40.78,CHN,,0,0,0,,也就是 e 的 -(x²+y²) 次方
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.78,0:13:42.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,You do have 1 degree of freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.78,0:13:42.60,CHN,,0,0,0,,确实还有1个自由度
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.60,0:13:44.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,to control the spread of that distribution
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.60,0:13:44.60,CHN,,0,0,0,,用来控制这个分布有多分散
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.60,0:13:47.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,and of course, there's going to be some constant sitting in front
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.60,0:13:47.06,CHN,,0,0,0,,前面也当然会有个常数
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.06,0:13:48.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,to make sure it's normalized
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.06,0:13:48.58,CHN,,0,0,0,,来确保总体积是 1
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.58,0:13:52.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,but the point is that we're forced into this very specific kind of bell curve shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.58,0:13:52.66,CHN,,0,0,0,,但无论如何 函数的形状必定是这种钟形
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.52,0:13:55.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,The first of these two properties
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.52,0:13:55.16,CHN,,0,0,0,,回到第一条要满足的性质
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.16,0:13:57.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,is that probability density around each point
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.16,0:13:57.98,CHN,,0,0,0,,每个点的概率密度
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.98,0:14:00.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,depends only on its distance from the origin
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.98,0:14:00.86,CHN,,0,0,0,,只取决于与原点的距离
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.86,0:14:02.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,not on its direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.86,0:14:02.42,CHN,,0,0,0,,而不取决于具体的方向
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.42,0:14:05.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,So, on a dartboard with everybody aiming for the bull's eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.42,0:14:05.44,CHN,,0,0,0,,用瞄准靶心射击来举例的话
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.44,0:14:07.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,this would mean that you could rotate the board
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.44,0:14:07.36,CHN,,0,0,0,,这就意味着  靶子旋转之后
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.36,0:14:09.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,and it would make no difference for the distribution.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.36,0:14:09.60,CHN,,0,0,0,,概率分布还是一样的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.48,0:14:13.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mathematically, this means that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.48,0:14:13.95,CHN,,0,0,0,,用数学语言来说的话
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.95,0:14:16.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,the function describing your probability distribution,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.95,0:14:16.66,CHN,,0,0,0,,考虑这一分布的概率密度函数
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.66,0:14:20.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,which I'll call f₂ since it takes in two inputs, X and Y.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.66,0:14:20.39,CHN,,0,0,0,,不妨记作 f₂(x,y)   因为有两个变量
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.39,0:14:21.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, it can be expressed as
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.39,0:14:21.61,CHN,,0,0,0,,则 f₂ 可以改写成
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.61,0:14:25.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,some single variable function of the radius, r.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.61,0:14:25.47,CHN,,0,0,0,,只关于半径 r 的单变量函数
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.47,0:14:26.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,And just to spell it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.47,0:14:26.62,CHN,,0,0,0,,重新明确一下
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.62,0:14:29.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,r is the distance between the point (x, y) and the origin,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.62,0:14:29.74,CHN,,0,0,0,,这里的 r 表示 (x, y) 离原点的距离
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.74,0:14:32.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,the square root of x² plus y².
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.74,0:14:32.88,CHN,,0,0,0,,也就是 {\fs0.001}l{\fs66\fsp0}√(x²+y²)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.88,0:14:34.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Property number 2 is that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.88,0:14:34.33,CHN,,0,0,0,,第二个性质是
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.33,0:14:38.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,the X and Y coordinates of each point are independent from each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.33,0:14:38.32,CHN,,0,0,0,,每个随机点的 x 值和 y 值相互独立
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.32,0:14:41.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Which is to say, if you learn the X coordinate of a point,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.32,0:14:41.14,CHN,,0,0,0,,也就是说  就算知道了一个点的横坐标 x
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.14,0:14:43.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,it would give you no information about the Y coordinate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.14,0:14:43.80,CHN,,0,0,0,,对点的纵坐标 y 来说  毫无信息量
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.11,0:14:47.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,The way this looks as an equation is that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.11,0:14:47.06,CHN,,0,0,0,,这个性质表现在式子里
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.06,0:14:49.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,our function which describes the probability density
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.53,0:14:51.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,around each point on the XY plane
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.06,0:14:51.65,CHN,,0,0,0,,就是这个表示各个点概率密度的函数
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.65,0:14:53.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,can be factored into two different parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.65,0:14:53.97,CHN,,0,0,0,,可以分离成两个函数的乘积
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.97,0:14:56.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,One of which can be purely written in terms of X.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.97,0:14:56.26,CHN,,0,0,0,,其中一个只有 x 变量
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.26,0:14:58.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is the distribution of the X coordinate,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.26,0:14:58.09,CHN,,0,0,0,,代表了横坐标值的概率分布
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.09,0:14:59.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm giving it the name "g".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.09,0:14:59.56,CHN,,0,0,0,,记作函数 g
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.56,0:15:01.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,And the other part is purely in terms of Y.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.56,0:15:01.99,CHN,,0,0,0,,而另一个函数则只有 y 变量
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.99,0:15:04.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,This would be the distribution for the Y coordinate
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.99,0:15:04.14,CHN,,0,0,0,,代表纵坐标值的概率分布
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.14,0:15:06.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,which I'm temporarily calling "h".
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.14,0:15:06.30,CHN,,0,0,0,,暂时叫做函数 h 好了
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.30,0:15:10.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,But if you combine this with the assumption that things are radially symmetric,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.30,0:15:10.00,CHN,,0,0,0,,但加上第一条假设  概率分布要径向对称
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.00,0:15:11.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,both of these should be the same distribution.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.00,0:15:11.99,CHN,,0,0,0,,那 x 和 y 的分布就得相同了
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.99,0:15:14.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,The behavior on each axis should look the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.99,0:15:14.39,CHN,,0,0,0,,也意味着两个轴上概率分布完全相同
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.39,0:15:17.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,So we could also write this as g(x)g(y).
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.39,0:15:17.39,CHN,,0,0,0,,于是这个式子可以写成 g(x)g(y)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.39,0:15:18.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's the same function.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.39,0:15:18.73,CHN,,0,0,0,,因为 g 恒等于 h
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.73,0:15:20.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,And more than that, this function is actually going to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.73,0:15:20.76,CHN,,0,0,0,,不仅如此  其实这个 g(x)g(y)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.76,0:15:23.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,be proportional to the one we were just looking at.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.76,0:15:23.21,CHN,,0,0,0,,还跟我们刚才考虑的 f 函数成正比
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.21,0:15:25.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,The one that describes our probability density
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.32,0:15:26.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,as a function of the radius,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.21,0:15:26.67,CHN,,0,0,0,,就是自变量为半径 r
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.67,0:15:28.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,the distance away from the origin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.67,0:15:28.61,CHN,,0,0,0,,的概率密度函数 f(r)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.61,0:15:31.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,To see this, imagine you were to analyze a point that was on the X axis,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.61,0:15:31.86,CHN,,0,0,0,,例如  假设有个 X 轴上的点
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.86,0:15:34.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,a distance r away from the origin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.86,0:15:34.17,CHN,,0,0,0,,离原点的距离是 r
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.17,0:15:36.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then the two distinct ways to express our function
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.17,0:15:36.56,CHN,,0,0,0,,那这两个基于不同性质构造的
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.56,0:15:38.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,based on the two different properties tells us that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.56,0:15:38.98,CHN,,0,0,0,,截然不同的概率分布函数形式
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.98,0:15:43.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,f(r) has to equal some constant multiplied by g(r).
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.98,0:15:43.10,CHN,,0,0,0,,表明了 f(r) 等于 g(r) 乘上一个常数
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.10,0:15:45.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,So these functions f and g are basically the same thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.10,0:15:45.90,CHN,,0,0,0,,也就说明了  函数 f 和 g 算是一种东西
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.90,0:15:47.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,just up to some constant multiple.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.90,0:15:47.71,CHN,,0,0,0,,只是差个常数倍
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.90,0:15:49.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,And you know what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.90,0:15:49.98,CHN,,0,0,0,,这时我就想了
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.10,0:15:53.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,It would be really nice if we could just assume that that constant was 1
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.10,0:15:53.67,CHN,,0,0,0,,直接说这个常数是 1 该多好啊
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.67,0:15:56.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,so that f and g were literally the same function
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.67,0:15:56.59,CHN,,0,0,0,,这样 f 和 g 不就完全相等了嘛
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.59,0:16:00.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,and what I'm going to do, which might feel a little bit cheeky
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.59,0:16:00.03,CHN,,0,0,0,,虽然很不要脸
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.03,0:16:02.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,is just assume that that is the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.03,0:16:02.08,CHN,,0,0,0,,但我想说我就是要这么做
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.08,0:16:04.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,What this means is that our answer is going to be a little bit wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.08,0:16:04.85,CHN,,0,0,0,,但这样的话  算出来的答案也就不这么准确了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.85,0:16:07.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,The function that we will deduce describing this distribution
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.85,0:16:07.61,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们得出的概率分布函数
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.61,0:16:09.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,will be off by some constant factor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.61,0:16:09.88,CHN,,0,0,0,,跟正确答案会差常数倍
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.88,0:16:11.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,But that's no big deal because in the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.88,0:16:11.94,CHN,,0,0,0,,但这根本就不是个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.94,0:16:14.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,we can just rescale to make sure the area under the curve is 1
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.94,0:16:14.87,CHN,,0,0,0,,最后我们还是得像其它概率分布一样
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.87,0:16:17.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,like we always do with probability distributions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.87,0:16:17.55,CHN,,0,0,0,,缩放一下  确保函数曲线下面积为 1
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.55,0:16:20.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, if f and g are the same thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.55,0:16:20.02,CHN,,0,0,0,,有了 f 和 g 等价
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.02,0:16:24.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,this gives us a very nice little equation purely in terms of the function f.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.02,0:16:24.46,CHN,,0,0,0,,就能得到这个只用 f 表示的式子
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.46,0:16:26.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,Remember what this function f is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.46,0:16:26.37,CHN,,0,0,0,,重复一下这个函数的含义
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.37,0:16:30.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you have some point in the XY plane, a distance r from the origin,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.37,0:16:30.32,CHN,,0,0,0,,假设平面上有一个离原点距离为 r 的点
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.32,0:16:31.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,then f(r) tells you the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.32,0:16:31.94,CHN,,0,0,0,,那么 f(r) 表示的是
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.94,0:16:35.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,relative likelihood of that point showing up in the random process.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.94,0:16:35.57,CHN,,0,0,0,,这个点在随机过程中出现的相对概率
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.57,0:16:39.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,More specifically, it gives the probability density of that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.57,0:16:39.05,CHN,,0,0,0,,也可以说成是这个点的概率密度
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.05,0:16:41.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,At the outset, this function could have been anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.05,0:16:41.67,CHN,,0,0,0,,一般来说  这个函数具体是什么并没有过多限制
Comment: 0,0:16:39.05,0:16:41.67,CHN,,0,0,0,,{\an7}#REVIEW 下面无穷积分得是 1（x
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.67,0:16:43.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,But Herschel's two different properties
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.67,0:16:43.35,CHN,,0,0,0,,但赫歇尔这两个性质
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.35,0:16:45.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,evidently implies something kind of funny about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.35,0:16:45.82,CHN,,0,0,0,,显然某种程度上影射了它的函数形式
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.82,0:16:49.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,Which is that if we take the X and Y coordinates of that point on the plane
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.82,0:16:49.31,CHN,,0,0,0,,也就是说  取平面上一个点的坐标 (x,y)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.31,0:16:54.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,and evaluate this function on them separately, taking f(x) times f(y)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.31,0:16:54.26,CHN,,0,0,0,,分别计算 f(x) 和 f(y) 再乘起来
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.26,0:16:56.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,it should give us the same result.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.26,0:16:56.38,CHN,,0,0,0,,结果应该和 f(r) 一致
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.38,0:16:58.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,Or if you prefer, we could expand out the meaning of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.74,0:17:01.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,that distance r as the square root of X² plus Y²
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.38,0:17:01.98,CHN,,0,0,0,,你也可以把距离 r 展开成 {\fs0.001}l{\fs66\fsp0}√(x²+y²)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.98,0:17:04.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,and this is what our key equation looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.98,0:17:04.01,CHN,,0,0,0,,得到一个关键的式子
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.00,0:17:09.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,This kind of equation is what's known in the business as a Functional Equation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.00,0:17:09.13,CHN,,0,0,0,,这种方程  内行的叫法是“函数方程”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.13,0:17:11.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're not solving for an unknown number.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.13,0:17:11.46,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们不是在求解一个未知数x
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.46,0:17:15.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Instead we're saying that the equation is true for all possible numbers X and Y
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.46,0:17:15.61,CHN,,0,0,0,,而是已知这个等式对所有的 x 和 y 都成立
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.61,0:17:18.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,and the thing we're trying to find is an unknown function.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.61,0:17:18.61,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们要找的是满足条件的未知函数 f(x)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.39,0:17:22.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,In the back of your mind, you can think we already know
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.39,0:17:22.66,CHN,,0,0,0,,在脑海中  我们已经知道了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.66,0:17:24.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,one function that satisfies this property,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.66,0:17:24.84,CHN,,0,0,0,,有一个函数满足这个性质
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.84,0:17:26.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,E to the negative X².
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.84,0:17:26.41,CHN,,0,0,0,,那就是 e 的 -x² 次方
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.41,0:17:27.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,And as a sanity check,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.41,0:17:27.53,CHN,,0,0,0,,检查一下
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.53,0:17:31.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,you might verify for yourself that it does satisfy that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.53,0:17:31.00,CHN,,0,0,0,,你会发现  函数确实满足这个方程
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.00,0:17:33.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Of course, the point is to pretend that you don't know that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.00,0:17:33.84,CHN,,0,0,0,,当然  重点是你要假装自己不知道这个函数
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.84,0:17:38.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,and to instead deduce what all of the functions are which satisfy this property.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.84,0:17:38.64,CHN,,0,0,0,,然后去推导  满足这个性质的函数都有哪些
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.64,0:17:41.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,In general, functional equations can be quite tricky.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.64,0:17:41.46,CHN,,0,0,0,,一般来说  函数方程没那么好解
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.46,0:17:43.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,But let me show you how you can solve this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.46,0:17:43.95,CHN,,0,0,0,,但这个方程我们可以这么求解
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.95,0:17:47.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,First it's nice to introduce a little helper function that I'll call h(x)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.95,0:17:47.90,CHN,,0,0,0,,首先  我们引入一个辅助函数 h(x)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.90,0:17:49.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,which will be defined as our mystery function
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.90,0:17:49.92,CHN,,0,0,0,,定义为我们要求的函数 -
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.92,0:17:52.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,evaluated at the square root of X.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.92,0:17:52.38,CHN,,0,0,0,,在 {\fs0.001}l{\fs66\fsp0}√x  点处的值
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.38,0:17:56.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Said another way, h(x²) is the same thing as f(x).
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.38,0:17:56.60,CHN,,0,0,0,,换句话说  h(x²) 就等于 f(x)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.60,0:17:58.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,For example, in the back of your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.60,0:17:58.32,CHN,,0,0,0,,例如  在脑海中
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.32,0:18:02.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,where you know that e^-x² will happen to be one of the answers,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.32,0:18:02.15,CHN,,0,0,0,,你知道 e 的 -x² 次方  已经是一个解
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.15,0:18:05.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,this little helper function h would be e^-x.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.15,0:18:05.84,CHN,,0,0,0,,那么它对应的辅助函数 h 就是 e⁻ˣ
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.84,0:18:08.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,But again, we're pretending like we don't know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.84,0:18:08.04,CHN,,0,0,0,,不过我们现在还是假装不知道答案
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.04,0:18:09.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,The reason for doing this is that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.04,0:18:09.36,CHN,,0,0,0,,引入辅助函数的原因是
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.36,0:18:11.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,the key property for f looks a little bit nicer
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.36,0:18:11.97,CHN,,0,0,0,,这会使函数 f 的关键性质变得更好看
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.97,0:18:14.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,if we phrase it in terms of this helper function, h.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.97,0:18:14.60,CHN,,0,0,0,,如果我们用 h 来表达 f 的性质
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.60,0:18:18.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,'Cuz now what it's saying is if you take two arbitrary positive numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.60,0:18:18.18,CHN,,0,0,0,,这个性质现在表示的就是  任取两个正数
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.18,0:18:20.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,and you add them up and evaluate h,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.18,0:18:20.21,CHN,,0,0,0,,先相加再代入函数 h
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.21,0:18:23.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,it's the same thing as evaluating h on them separately
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.22,0:18:24.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,and then multiplying the results.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.21,0:18:24.94,CHN,,0,0,0,,结果等于  先分别代入函数 h  再相乘
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.94,0:18:27.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,In a sense, it turns addition into multiplication.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.94,0:18:27.94,CHN,,0,0,0,,可以说   h 将加法变成了乘法
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.94,0:18:29.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,Some of you might see where this is going
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.94,0:18:29.89,CHN,,0,0,0,,有些观众可能已经有头绪了
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.89,0:18:31.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,but let's take a moment to walk through
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.89,0:18:31.47,CHN,,0,0,0,,但我们还是先花时间过一遍
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.47,0:18:32.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,why this forces our hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.47,0:18:32.99,CHN,,0,0,0,,这性质为什么定死了答案
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.40,0:18:37.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,As a next step, you might want to pause and convince yourself that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.40,0:18:37.07,CHN,,0,0,0,,接下来  你可能需要暂停一下并搞清楚
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.07,0:18:39.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,if this property is true for the sum of two numbers,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.07,0:18:39.84,CHN,,0,0,0,,如果这个性质对于两个正数的和成立
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.84,0:18:43.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,this property also must be true if we add up an arbitrary number of inputs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.84,0:18:43.99,CHN,,0,0,0,,那么  将任意 n 个数相加再代入 h   这个性质依旧成立
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.21,0:18:47.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,To get a feel for why this is so constraining,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.21,0:18:47.42,CHN,,0,0,0,,为了感受一下这个约束条件有多强
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.42,0:18:51.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,think about plugging in a whole number, something like h(5).
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.42,0:18:51.20,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们代入一个具体数值  比如求 h(5)
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.20,0:18:55.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Because you can write five as one plus one plus one plus one plus one,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.20,0:18:55.10,CHN,,0,0,0,,因为你可以将 5 写成 1+1+1+1+1
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.10,0:18:56.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,this key property means that it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.10,0:18:56.60,CHN,,0,0,0,,这个关键的性质意味着
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.60,0:19:00.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,must equal h(1) multiplied by itself five times.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.60,0:19:00.98,CHN,,0,0,0,,h(5) 一定等于 h(1) 与自己相乘五次的结果
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.98,0:19:02.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,Of course, there's nothing special about five,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.98,0:19:02.79,CHN,,0,0,0,,当然  这里的 5 并无特殊之处
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.79,0:19:05.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,I could have chosen any whole number N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.79,0:19:05.16,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们可以选择任何整数 N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.16,0:19:06.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,and we'd be forced to that the function
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.16,0:19:06.97,CHN,,0,0,0,,然后我们带入函数 h 中
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.97,0:19:09.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,looks like some number raised to the power N,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.97,0:19:09.82,CHN,,0,0,0,,结果就等于 h(1) 的 N 次方
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.80,0:19:12.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,and let's go ahead and give that number a name
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.80,0:19:12.89,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们直接给这个 h(1) 取个名字
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.89,0:19:15.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,like "b" for the base of our exponential.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.89,0:19:15.09,CHN,,0,0,0,,记作 b   表示指数函数的底数
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.07,0:19:17.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,As a little mini exercise here,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.07,0:19:17.72,CHN,,0,0,0,,接下来有一个小练习
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.72,0:19:20.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,see if you can pause and take a moment to convince yourself that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.72,0:19:20.27,CHN,,0,0,0,,暂停并思考一下  看看你能不能证明
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.27,0:19:22.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,the same is true for a rational input.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.27,0:19:22.52,CHN,,0,0,0,,这个结论对于有理数也同样成立
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.52,0:19:25.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,That if you plug in p/q to this function,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.52,0:19:25.34,CHN,,0,0,0,,也就是说  如果你把 p/q 代入函数
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.34,0:19:29.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,it must look like this base b^p/q.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.34,0:19:29.19,CHN,,0,0,0,,结果也一定和 b 的 p/q 次方相等
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.60,0:19:32.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,And as a hint, you might want to think about
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.60,0:19:32.50,CHN,,0,0,0,,再给一个小提示  你或许会需要考虑
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.50,0:19:35.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,adding that input to itself q different times.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.50,0:19:35.40,CHN,,0,0,0,,将这个 p/q 与自己相加 q 次
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.51,0:19:41.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,And then because rational numbers are dense in the real number line,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.51,0:19:41.89,CHN,,0,0,0,,接下来因为有理数在实数轴上是稠密的
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.89,0:19:44.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,if we make one more pretty reasonable assumption that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.89,0:19:44.24,CHN,,0,0,0,,如果我们再做一个挺合理的假设
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.24,0:19:46.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,we only care about continuous functions,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.24,0:19:46.54,CHN,,0,0,0,,假设我们只关心连续函数
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.54,0:19:49.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,this is enough to force your hand completely and say that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.54,0:19:49.05,CHN,,0,0,0,,这就足够迫使我们得出结论
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.05,0:19:55.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,h has to be an exponential function, b^x for all real number inputs x.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.05,0:19:55.20,CHN,,0,0,0,,h 一定是指数函数   h(x) = bˣ
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.20,0:19:58.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,I guess to be more precise, I should say for all positive real inputs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.20,0:19:58.62,CHN,,0,0,0,,更准确点  我应该说 b 和 x 都是正实数
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.62,0:20:02.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,The way we defined h it's only taking in positive numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.62,0:20:02.35,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们定义的函数 h 本来就只接受正数
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.35,0:20:04.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, as we've gone over before,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.35,0:20:04.13,CHN,,0,0,0,,接着  上期视频也讨论过
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.13,0:20:08.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,instead of writing down exponential functions as some base raised to the power x,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.13,0:20:08.09,CHN,,0,0,0,,与其把指数函数写为某个底数 b 的 x 次方
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.09,0:20:13.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,mathematicians often to write them as e to the power of some constant c times x.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.09,0:20:13.24,CHN,,0,0,0,,数学家们更爱写 e 的“常数 c 乘以 x”次方
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.24,0:20:15.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Making the choice to always use e as a base
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.24,0:20:15.66,CHN,,0,0,0,,一直选用 e 作为底数
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.66,0:20:17.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,while letting that constant c determine
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.66,0:20:17.58,CHN,,0,0,0,,再用参数 c 来确定
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.58,0:20:20.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,which specific exponential function you are talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.58,0:20:20.35,CHN,,0,0,0,,你讨论的是哪个具体的指数函数
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.35,0:20:24.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,just makes everything much easier anytime calculus comes wandering along your path.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.35,0:20:24.70,CHN,,0,0,0,,这样万一要做微积分的计算  也会变得更方便
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.76,0:20:28.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,And so, this means that our target function f
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.76,0:20:28.68,CHN,,0,0,0,,同样  这也意味着我们的目标函数 f
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.68,0:20:33.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,has to look like e^cx².
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.68,0:20:33.50,CHN,,0,0,0,,应该是“e 的 cx² 次方”这样的形式
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.50,0:20:35.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,The beauty is that that function is no longer something
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.72,0:20:38.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,that was merely handed down to us from on high.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.50,0:20:38.64,CHN,,0,0,0,,这套推导的好处在于  这个函数不再是凭空而来
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.64,0:20:40.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,Instead, we started these two different premises
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.64,0:20:40.98,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们是从两个前提条件出发
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.98,0:20:44.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,for how we wanted a distribution in two dimensions to behave
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.98,0:20:44.47,CHN,,0,0,0,,寻找我们想要的二元概率分布
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.47,0:20:46.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,and we were drawn to the conclusion that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.47,0:20:46.14,CHN,,0,0,0,,并且我们得到的结论是
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.14,0:20:49.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,the shape of the expression describing that distribution
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.14,0:20:49.14,CHN,,0,0,0,,这个分布的密度可以表示为一个
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.14,0:20:51.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,as a function of the radius away from the origin
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.14,0:20:51.74,CHN,,0,0,0,,以半径 r 为自变量的函数
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.74,0:20:55.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,has to be e to the power of some constant times that radius squared.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.74,0:20:55.30,CHN,,0,0,0,,且形式一定是 e 的（常数 c 乘以半径 r 平方）次方
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.20,0:20:59.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,You remember I said earlier this answer will be off by a factor of a constant.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.20,0:20:59.94,CHN,,0,0,0,,你应该记得我之前说过  这个答案还会差一个常数
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.94,0:21:03.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,We need to rescale it to make it a valid probability distribution
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.94,0:21:03.18,CHN,,0,0,0,,我们要缩放常数   使整个函数成为真正的概率分布
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.18,0:21:05.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,and geometrically, you might think of that as scaling it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.18,0:21:05.35,CHN,,0,0,0,,从几何上讲  你可以认为缩放后
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.35,0:21:07.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,so that the volume under the surface is equal to 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.35,0:21:07.98,CHN,,0,0,0,,曲面下方的体积必须等于 1
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.80,0:21:13.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now you notice that for positive values of this constant in the exponent c,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.80,0:21:13.19,CHN,,0,0,0,,可以注意到  如果指数中的常数 c 为正值
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.19,0:21:16.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,our function blows up to infinity in all directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.19,0:21:16.18,CHN,,0,0,0,,函数就会在所有方向上都膨胀到无穷大
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.18,0:21:18.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,So, the volume under that surface would be infinite,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.18,0:21:18.58,CHN,,0,0,0,,因此  曲面下方的体积就会是无穷大的
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.58,0:21:20.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,meaning it's not possible to renormalize.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.58,0:21:20.84,CHN,,0,0,0,,意味着我们不可能将其归一化
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.84,0:21:23.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,You can't turn it into a probability distribution
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.84,0:21:23.52,CHN,,0,0,0,,也就无法把它变成一个概率分布
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.52,0:21:25.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,and that leaves us with the last constraint
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.52,0:21:25.79,CHN,,0,0,0,,这就是最后一个约束条件
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.79,0:21:29.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,which is that this constant in the exponent has to be a negative number
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.79,0:21:29.06,CHN,,0,0,0,,指数中的常数c  必须是一个负值
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.06,0:21:32.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,and the specific value of that number determines the spread of the distribution.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.06,0:21:32.89,CHN,,0,0,0,,并且这个特定的常数决定了分布的分散度
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.85,0:21:35.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,10 years after Herschel wrote this,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.85,0:21:35.90,CHN,,0,0,0,,在赫歇尔写下这个结论十年后
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.90,0:21:38.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,James Clerk Maxwell, who's most well known for having written down
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.83,0:21:41.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,the fundamental equations for electricity and magnetism,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.90,0:21:41.58,CHN,,0,0,0,,以写下电与磁的基本方程而闻名的麦克斯韦
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.58,0:21:44.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,independently stumbled across the same derivation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.58,0:21:44.23,CHN,,0,0,0,,也刚好独立地进行了相同的推导
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.23,0:21:46.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,In his case, he was doing it in three dimensions
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.23,0:21:46.54,CHN,,0,0,0,,但他考虑的是三维空间中的分布
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.54,0:21:49.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,since he was doing statistical mechanics and he was deriving
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.54,0:21:49.16,CHN,,0,0,0,,因为他当时正在研究统计力学
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.16,0:21:53.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,a formula for the distribution for velocities of molecules in a gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.16,0:21:53.33,CHN,,0,0,0,,需要推导气体中分子速度分布的公式
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.33,0:21:55.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,but the logic all works out the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.33,0:21:55.85,CHN,,0,0,0,,但背后的逻辑都是一样的
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.85,0:22:00.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,For you and me, if we view this as the defining property of a Gaussian,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.85,0:22:00.44,CHN,,0,0,0,,如果我们认为  这两个性质{\u1}定义{\u0}了高斯分布的话
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.44,0:22:03.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,then it's a little bit less surprising that π might make an appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.44,0:22:03.81,CHN,,0,0,0,,那么 π 的出现也就不那么意外了
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.81,0:22:08.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,After all, circular symmetry was part of this defining property.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.81,0:22:08.04,CHN,,0,0,0,,毕竟  圆形对称也是这个定义性质的一部分
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.04,0:22:10.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,More than that, it makes the clever proof that we saw earlier
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.04,0:22:10.82,CHN,,0,0,0,,更重要的是  它让我们之前看到的美妙证明
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.82,0:22:13.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,feel a little bit less out of the blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.82,0:22:13.09,CHN,,0,0,0,,变得不那么出乎意料
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.09,0:22:15.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,I mean, a key problem solve principle in math
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.09,0:22:15.78,CHN,,0,0,0,,你看  数学中有个关键的解题原则是
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.78,0:22:18.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,is to use the defining features of your setup.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.78,0:22:18.57,CHN,,0,0,0,,使用你开始时设定好的定义
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.57,0:22:22.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,And if you had been primed by this Herschel/Maxwell derivation
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.57,0:22:22.34,CHN,,0,0,0,,如果你跟上了 赫歇尔-麦克斯韦 的推导
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.34,0:22:24.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,where the defining property for a Gaussian
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.34,0:22:24.31,CHN,,0,0,0,,其中为高斯分布设的定义性质是
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.31,0:22:26.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,is this coincidence of having a distribution
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.31,0:22:26.85,CHN,,0,0,0,,这一类分布  需要同时满足
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.85,0:22:31.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,that's both radially symmetric and also independent along each axis,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.85,0:22:31.17,CHN,,0,0,0,,1.径向对称性  与  2.各坐标独立分布
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.17,0:22:34.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,then the very first step of our proof which seemed so strange,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.17,0:22:34.49,CHN,,0,0,0,,那么在我们的证明中  看着很奇怪的第一步
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.49,0:22:36.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,bumping the problem up one dimension,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.49,0:22:36.44,CHN,,0,0,0,,即  将问题提升一个维度
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.44,0:22:38.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,was really just a way of opening the door
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.44,0:22:38.46,CHN,,0,0,0,,实际上就是在打开一扇门
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.46,0:22:41.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,to let that defining property make itself visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.46,0:22:41.31,CHN,,0,0,0,,方便具体体现两条定义性质
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.18,0:22:43.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,And if you think back,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.18,0:22:43.27,CHN,,0,0,0,,如果你回想一下
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.27,0:22:47.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,the essence of the came down to using that radial symmetry on the one hand
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.27,0:22:47.45,CHN,,0,0,0,,证明的核心  一方面利用了函数的径向对称性
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.45,0:22:51.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,and then also using the ability to factor the function on the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.45,0:22:51.30,CHN,,0,0,0,,而另一方面则利用了函数可分解的性质
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.30,0:22:53.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,From this standpoint, using both those facts
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.30,0:22:53.60,CHN,,0,0,0,,从这个角度来看  使用这两个事实
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.60,0:22:56.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,feels less like a trick that happens to work
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.60,0:22:56.11,CHN,,0,0,0,,感觉就不那么像是碰巧的小把戏
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.11,0:22:58.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,and more like an inevitable necessity.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.11,0:22:58.49,CHN,,0,0,0,,而更像是不可避免的步骤
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.19,0:23:03.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, thinking once again of our statistician's friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.19,0:23:03.90,CHN,,0,0,0,,然而  再次回想起统计学家的朋友
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.90,0:23:06.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,this is still not entirely satisfying.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.90,0:23:06.25,CHN,,0,0,0,,这仍然不完全令人满意
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.25,0:23:08.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Using the Herschel/Maxwell derivation,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.25,0:23:08.48,CHN,,0,0,0,,赫歇尔-麦克斯韦的推导
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.48,0:23:12.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,saying this property of a multi-dimensional distribution is what defines a Gaussian,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.48,0:23:12.94,CHN,,0,0,0,,以及  用高维分布的两个性质去定义高斯分布
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.94,0:23:14.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,well that presumes that we're already in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.71,0:23:17.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,some kind of multi-dimensional situation in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.94,0:23:17.96,CHN,,0,0,0,,首先要求我们已经处在某种多维情形中
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.96,0:23:22.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,Much more commonly, the way that a normal distribution arises in practice
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.96,0:23:22.16,CHN,,0,0,0,,通常来说  实际上正态分布出现的情形
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.16,0:23:24.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,doesn't feel spatial or geometric at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.16,0:23:24.84,CHN,,0,0,0,,感觉跟空间与几何不相干
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.84,0:23:26.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,It stems from the central limit theorem
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.84,0:23:26.89,CHN,,0,0,0,,而是来源于中心极限定理
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.89,0:23:30.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,which is all about adding together many different independent variables.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.89,0:23:30.66,CHN,,0,0,0,,讲的都是关于将许多独立的随机变量相加
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.66,0:23:33.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,So to bring it all home here, what we need to do is explain
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.66,0:23:33.91,CHN,,0,0,0,,因此  回到最开始  我们需要去解释
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.91,0:23:37.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,why the function that's characterized by this Herschel/Maxwell derivation
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.91,0:23:37.74,CHN,,0,0,0,,为什么这个  赫歇尔-麦克斯韦的推导所刻画的函数
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.74,0:23:39.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,should be the same thing as
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.20,0:23:42.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,the function that sits at the heart of the central limit theorem.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.74,0:23:42.42,CHN,,0,0,0,,会等价于  中心极限定理中最核心的函数  呢
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.42,0:23:45.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,And at this point, those of you following along
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.42,0:23:45.17,CHN,,0,0,0,,看到这里  跟随我一路看下来的观众
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.17,0:23:46.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,are probably going to make fun of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.17,0:23:46.84,CHN,,0,0,0,,可能会来取笑我
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.84,0:23:50.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,I think it makes sense to pull this last step as its own video.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.84,0:23:50.26,CHN,,0,0,0,,虽然我认为把最后一步单独做成视频是有意义的
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.26,0:23:51.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,I realise this is what?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.26,0:23:51.65,CHN,,0,0,0,,不过我意识到这…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.65,0:23:55.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,The third time in a row that I've kicked this particular can down the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.65,0:23:55.54,CHN,,0,0,0,,已经是我第三次把这话题鸽到下一期了
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.54,0:23:57.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,You see, the thing I'm building up to here
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.54,0:23:57.41,CHN,,0,0,0,,要知道  我所铺垫的下一期内容
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.41,0:24:00.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,involves a combination of the topics from the last three videos -
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.41,0:24:00.66,CHN,,0,0,0,,将同时涉及到这三期视频的主题
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.66,0:24:02.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Convolutions, the Central Limit Theorem
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.66,0:24:02.72,CHN,,0,0,0,,卷积  中心极限定理
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.72,0:24:07.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,and now the Herschel/Maxwell characterization of normal distributions.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.72,0:24:07.02,CHN,,0,0,0,,以及  赫歇尔/麦克斯韦对正态分布的刻画
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.02,0:24:10.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,The traditional explanation that I first learned to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.02,0:24:10.08,CHN,,0,0,0,,我第一次学会的传统解释方法解释了
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.08,0:24:13.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,why e^-x² arises in the central limit theorem
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.08,0:24:13.60,CHN,,0,0,0,,为什么 e 的 -x² 次方会出现在中心极限定理中
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.60,0:24:16.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,has to do with fourier transforms and the convolution theorem
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.60,0:24:16.79,CHN,,0,0,0,,用到了傅里叶变换和卷积定理
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.79,0:24:18.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,and it's nice enough, don't get me wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.79,0:24:18.57,CHN,,0,0,0,,别误会  我并不是说那个证明不好
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.57,0:24:21.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,but what I'd like to try is to share a more elementary description
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.57,0:24:21.74,CHN,,0,0,0,,只是我希望分享一个更为初等的证明
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.74,0:24:24.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,that's based on this circular symmetry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.74,0:24:24.12,CHN,,0,0,0,,而且会妙用圆形对称性
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.12,0:24:26.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,The hope is that, together with this video,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.12,0:24:26.08,CHN,,0,0,0,,我希望  结合这期视频
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.08,0:24:30.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,it offers a more visceral satisfaction for why that particular function arises
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.08,0:24:30.88,CHN,,0,0,0,,搞清楚这种函数的来龙去脉  能让你的满足感油然而生
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.88,0:24:33.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,and that maybe it offers something which would finally
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.88,0:24:33.16,CHN,,0,0,0,,并且这也可能会提供一些
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.16,0:24:35.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,address the incredulity from our statistician's friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.16,0:24:35.90,CHN,,0,0,0,,最终解决我们统计学家朋友的疑问的想法
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.18,0:24:41.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh and one final footnote here -
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.18,0:24:41.36,CHN,,0,0,0,,哦  还有最后一个脚注
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.36,0:24:44.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,after making a Patreon post about this particular project,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.36,0:24:44.51,CHN,,0,0,0,,当在 Patreon 发布了一篇关于这个特定项目的推文后
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.51,0:24:47.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,one Patron who's a mathematician named Kevin Iga,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.51,0:24:47.38,CHN,,0,0,0,,有位赞助者名叫 Kevin Iga，是一名数学家
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.38,0:24:50.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,shared something completely delightful that I'd never seen before,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.38,0:24:50.53,CHN,,0,0,0,,Ta 分享了一些  让我大开眼界的美妙结果
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.53,0:24:54.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,which is that if you apply this integration trick in higher dimensions,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.53,0:24:54.24,CHN,,0,0,0,,如果你在更高的维度上运用这个积分技巧
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.24,0:24:58.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,it lets you derive the formulas for volumes of higher dimensional spheres.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.24,0:24:58.14,CHN,,0,0,0,,它可以带你推导出更高维球体的体积公式
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.14,0:25:01.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's a very fun exercise, I'm leaving the details up on the screen
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.14,0:25:01.14,CHN,,0,0,0,,这个练习非常有趣  我会将细节放在屏幕上
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.14,0:25:04.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,for any viewers who are comfortable with integration by parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.14,0:25:04.24,CHN,,0,0,0,,能熟练运用分部积分的观众们  都可以来尝试一下
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.24,0:25:06.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much to Kevin for sharing that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.24,0:25:06.55,CHN,,0,0,0,,非常感谢 Kevin 分享这一点
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.55,0:25:08.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,And thanks to all patrons by the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.55,0:25:08.07,CHN,,0,0,0,,也顺便感谢所有赞助者
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.07,0:25:09.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,both for the support of the channel
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.07,0:25:09.54,CHN,,0,0,0,,感谢你们对于这个频道的支持
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.54,0:25:12.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,and also for all the feedback you offer on the early draft videos.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.54,0:25:12.68,CHN,,0,0,0,,也感谢你们对于视频草稿提供的所有反馈
